AFTER a year-long absence in the local soccer calender, the Carling Black Label Cup returns on Saturday, with Soweto giants Kaizer Chiefs and Orlando Pirates taking each other on in what has become the traditional curtain-raiser ahead of the new season. The 2018 edition of the pre-season tournament was cancelled, with the competition’s sponsor throwing its weight behind a much bigger event, the Fifa World Cup in Russia. However, with the global spectacle all but a distant memory, Soweto’s finest are back in the centre stage in what is a unique fixture in how it gets the fans involved by voting in who they would prefer to see in the starting line-up of either team. CARLING BLACK LABEL CUP FACTS